{
  "name": "n8n Backup GitOps",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## n8n Backup GitOps\n\nBackup incremental de workflows n8n no GitHub.\nSalva apenas os workflows que foram modificados desde o último backup (compara `versionId`).\n\n**Como configurar:**\n1. `1. Listar Workflows` e `6. Export Completo` → preencha a URL da instância n8n e a API Key\n2. `3. Buscar GitHub`, `8b` e `8c` → conecte sua credencial GitHub e ajuste a URL do repo\n3. `10. Notificar` → conecte sua credencial Evolution API (ou remova o nó)\n\n**Pastas:** primeira tag do workflow = pasta no GitHub. Sem tag → `Uncategorized/`\n\n---\nCriado por [@erick.fonsec](https://www.instagram.com/erick.fonsec/) · [EFS Studio](https://efsstudio.com.br) · MIT License",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 7
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1440,
        -240
      ],
      "id": "sticky-credits",
      "name": "Créditos"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "weeks",
              "triggerAtDay": [
                5
              ],
              "triggerAtHour": 3
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        -1440,
        64
      ],
      "id": "f8d8b0a6-7f62-41a0-affe-cd02e4460f16",
      "name": "Toda Sexta 3h"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "https://n8n.SEUDOMINIO.COM/api/v1/workflows",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "X-N8N-API-KEY",
              "value": "SUA_CHAVE_API"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "responseFormat": "json"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        -1200,
        64
      ],
      "id": "578a6178-8ca9-4a40-851c-23f3ae934550",
      "name": "1. Listar Workflows"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const response = $('1. Listar Workflows').first().json;\nconst workflows = response.data || response;\n\nfunction slugify(text) {\n  const map = {'á':'a','à':'a','ã':'a','â':'a','é':'e','ê':'e','í':'i',\n               'ó':'o','ô':'o','õ':'o','ú':'u','ü':'u','ç':'c'};\n  let slug = text.toLowerCase();\n  for (const [k, v] of Object.entries(map)) slug = slug.split(k).join(v);\n  slug = slug.replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').replace(/-+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, '');\n  return slug.substring(0, 60);\n}\n\n// ─── Pasta = primeira tag do workflow ────────────────────────\n// Toda tag vira pasta automaticamente.\n// Múltiplas tags → primeira tag é a pasta principal\n// Sem tag alguma → Uncategorized\nfunction getFolder(tags) {\n  if (tags.length === 0) return 'Uncategorized';\n  return tags[0];\n}\n\nconst items = workflows.map(w => {\n  const tags = (w.tags || []).map(t => typeof t === 'string' ? t : t.name || '');\n  const folder = getFolder(tags);\n  const slug = slugify(w.name);\n  const filename = slug + '.json';\n  const githubPath = 'workflows/' + folder + '/' + filename;\n  return {\n    json: {\n      workflowId: w.id,\n      workflowName: w.name,\n      versionId: w.versionId,\n      tags,\n      folder,\n      filename,\n      githubPath\n    }\n  };\n});\n\nreturn items;"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -960,
        64
      ],
      "id": "4af127a2-211a-4ac6-99e0-0c2df6baad4e",
      "name": "2. Split + Organizar"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "=https://api.github.com/repos/SEU_USUARIO/SEU_REPOSITORIO/contents/{{ $json.githubPath }}",
        "authentication": "predefinedCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "githubApi",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        -720,
        64
      ],
      "id": "dd1e1f84-7683-483b-9a2c-3ee2954e61fd",
      "name": "3. Buscar GitHub",
      "credentials": {
        "githubApi": {
          "id": "",
          "name": "GitHub API"
        }
      },
      "onError": "continueRegularOutput"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const splitItems = $('2. Split + Organizar').all();\nconst ghItems = $('3. Buscar GitHub').all();\n\nconst results = [];\nfor (let i = 0; i < splitItems.length; i++) {\n  const original = splitItems[i].json;\n  const ghData = ghItems[i] ? ghItems[i].json : {};\n\n  let savedVersionId = '';\n  let fileSha = '';\n\n  const rawContent = ghData.content || '';\n  const rawSha     = ghData.sha     || '';\n\n  if (rawSha) fileSha = rawSha;\n\n  if (rawContent) {\n    try {\n      const cleaned  = rawContent.replace(/\\n/g, '');\n      const decoded  = Buffer.from(cleaned, 'base64').toString('utf-8');\n      const parsed   = JSON.parse(decoded);\n      savedVersionId = parsed.versionId || '';\n    } catch(e) {}\n  }\n\n  const hasChanges = original.versionId !== savedVersionId;\n\n  results.push({\n    json: { ...original, savedVersionId, fileSha, hasChanges }\n  });\n}\n\nreturn results;"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -480,
        64
      ],
      "id": "41600a2f-3094-4db2-82cb-c25bed8607ab",
      "name": "4. Comparar versionId"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict",
            "version": 2
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "chg",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.hasChanges }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "true",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [
        -240,
        64
      ],
      "id": "6ff07916-c064-46db-8f8f-932f8759f606",
      "name": "5. Mudou?"
    },
